{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"92adeb87-6ec5-49f0-af48-7b5820320aac","content":"There's no `SettingsPage.xaml` in the current directory — so I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n### Converting to compiled bindings\n\nAdd the `x:DataType` attribute to your `ContentPage`, pointing at your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <StackLayout Padding=\"20\">\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Slider Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"40\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**What changed:** Only `xmlns:vm` and `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` were added. Every `{Binding}` inside the page is now compiled against that type — if you typo a property name (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`), the compiler will emit an error like:\n\n```\nXC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\".\n```\n\n### Catching binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings already produce **build errors** for missing/mistyped properties. To make the net even tighter:\n\n1. **Enable `$(TreatXamlWarningsAsErrors)`** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TreatXamlWarningsAsErrors>true</TreatXamlWarningsAsErrors>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n   This promotes XAML warnings (XC*) to errors so they can't be ignored.\n\n2. **Opt out selectively** — if a binding must be late-bound (e.g., inside a `DataTemplate` whose type varies), use `x:DataType=\"\"` to disable compiled bindings for that subtree only.\n\n3. **Build with `dotnet build`** — the XAML compiler runs during the normal build; no extra flags needed.\n\nThat's all it takes: `x:DataType` on the root element, and optionally `TreatXamlWarningsAsErrors` in the project file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"00c22dea-ea21-48c0-a656-d136532c75b2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no files in the working directory. The user is asking me to help them convert a hypothetical page. Let me provide guidance on how to do this, since there's no actual file to modify. I'll explain the conversion and how to catch errors at build time.\n\nActually, let me check what's in the working directory first.","outputTokens":674},"id":"fe04ea40-964f-4b8d-9739-f9bf8910cc9e","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:57:28.916Z","parentId":"8bed5a50-35a4-4c80-a455-f48569f6ec70"}
